
Password in arguments:
otiicli --server --username <username> --password <password> --reserve-time <reserve-time>

Or prompt for password:
otiicli --server --username <username> --prompt --reserve-time <reserve-time>




Options:
  -h, --help                         Displays this help.
  -d, --device <device>              Restrict usage to device
  -l, --list-devices                 List available devices
  -n, --no-banner                    Omit the version banner
  -v, --verbose                      Verbose output
  -V, --version                      Show application version
  -L, --license                      Show current license status
  -u, --username <username>          Username
  -p, --password <password>          Password
  -P, --prompt                       Prompt for password
  -t, --reserve-time <reserve-time>  License reserve time in seconds
  -r, --return                       Return license when exiting                    <-- THIS
  -R, --logout                       Return license and logout when exiting         <-- THIS
  -s, --server                       Start Otii TCP-Server

Arguments:
  script                             Script to run
  args                               Optional script arguments


Stop server with ctrl-c

